Master Answer: Yes, your daughter is eligible to receive vaccines provided as part of the school-based program for free.  We recommend that you take your daughter's immunization record to your local public health unit to be checked. Vaccine recommendations and schedules differ between countries.  A public health nurse can review your daughter's record and recommend and provide any missing vaccines. You can find the contact information for your local public health unit here.
